What is the content of your APK? You can see this with e.g. unzip -v tensorflow_demo.apk

Note that you need all the .so files present at the highest architecture level any of them are present at. So if you have one added to your apk in libs/arm64-v8a, all of the others used need to be in that directory as well.

body:
What is the content of your APK? You can see this with e.g. `unzip -v tensorflow_demo.apk`

Note that you need all the .so files present at the highest architecture level any of them are present at. So if you have one added to your apk in libs/arm64-v8a, all of the others used need to be in that directory as well.
